Variation in the expression levels due to allele-dosage effects can be expected in polyploids, and this could lead to variable phenotypic effects 42 . Appropriate knowledge of allele dosage in polyploid organisms is required to test for allele-specific expression. ASE tests used in diploids are often based on a Binomial distribution using the null hypothesis that both alleles are expressed equally ( θ = 0.5 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
